It is the dagobah tree. You get what you bring with you. I loved it, because I was willing to accept the rule of cool.

The latest edition to Skywalker Saga is profoundly unique. It pays homage to previous films created in the storyline but still does a fantastic job in giving the franchise a new spin. 

As a Star Wars fan I admire the way the film respects previously developed characters and continues (ultimately finishing) their arcs. I also appreciated the way the film integrated the element if mystery and adventure that has become synonymous with other films in this franchise. As a film buff I admired the messages that it poses to its viewers and the unique ways that only a Star Wars film can present them.

At times early in the film it does seem like the story is rushed due to the fact that transitions from scene to scene are ineffective. Ultimately giving the viewer the feeling of a prolonged rising action just for the movie to slow down and continue progression to the climax. None-the-less all of the information that is presented is needed in order to create an effective climax which the film achieves. 

Which is the reason why I give a 4/5, the film pulls several different emotions out of the viewer as it should. If my rating was based on percentage it would be an 87%.
